## Results

The fair global r is **{{ metrics.fair_mean | fmt }}**, consistent with the 0.44–0.52 range
seen in other drug-blind benchmarks on GDSC2. From this baseline, two protocol choices
inflate the headline figure. Test-set snooping adds +{{ metrics.inflation | fmt }},
bringing the PASO-style mean to {{ metrics.paso_style_mean | fmt }}. Selecting the
single best fold rather than reporting the mean adds a further
+{{ (metrics.best_fold_test_r - metrics.paso_style_mean) | fmt }},
producing a headline figure of {{ metrics.best_fold_test_r | fmt }}, approximately
matching the published {{ metrics.paso_reported_r | fmt }}.
Total inflation from the fair mean to the reported figure is **+{{ (metrics.best_fold_test_r - metrics.fair_mean) | fmt }}**.

